{
"Theorem": "Let A be a square matrix. If A^2 is invertible then A is also invertible.",
"Proof": "Assume A is not invertible. Then it has a zero determinant. Because the determinant of A^2 is the square of the determinant of A, if A has a zero determinant, then A^2 will also have a zero determinant, implying A^2 is not invertible. This contradicts the assumption that A^2 is invertible. Therefore, the assumption that A is not invertible must be false, implying A is invertible."
}
